Sentencas: Gas-tight electrolyte films are obtained by chemical vapor deposition for solid oxide fuel cells from yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) with a thickness of 4-15 mu m on supporting porous ceramic anodes (YSZ/NiO).
Titulo: Chemical vapor deposition of electrolyte thin films based on yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: Volatile metal complexes with dipivaloylmethane Zr(dpm)(4) and Y(dpm)(3) are used as precursors.
Titulo: Chemical vapor deposition of electrolyte thin films based on yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: On the basis of an analysis of thermal properties of the starting compounds, parameter ranges in deposition processes are determined.
Titulo: Chemical vapor deposition of electrolyte thin films based on yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: Dependences of the structure, composition, and electrical characteristics on deposition conditions are found for YSZ electrolyte films.
Titulo: Chemical vapor deposition of electrolyte thin films based on yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: Electrochemical solid oxide fuel cells that operate at low temperatures with an open circuit voltage of 0.98-1.08 V and specific power up to 440 mW/cm(2) at 1073 K and 1200 mW/cm(2) at 1173 K are constructed.
Titulo: Chemical vapor deposition of electrolyte thin films based on yttria-stabilized zirconia
